review_blob: Tastes and smells fruity. Cant quite put a finger on the other aromas/flavors.
Newcastle was the first brown ale I ever tried, and I loved it. My opinion has changed since Ive tried others. Nutty malt flavor, but pretty weak.
Normally not really a fan of IPAs but this one was pretty solid. Tasted slightly above average for this style.
Beautiful color, nice raspberry aroma. However, it was so sweet that I could barely drink more than 2 glasses.
Smells and tastes like the perfect mixture of coffee and beer. Great drink to start off the night.
